          <desc type="abstract" xml:id="abstract5276-1" xml:lang="en" source="#bib5276-2"><quote>[T]he largest river in southern Persia. It rises in the north-eastern part of the district of ʿArabistān (earlier called K̲h̲ūzistān), a little above Lat. 32º N. on the Zarda-Kūh, which belongs to the Bak̲h̲tiyārī mountain system or, to be more accurate, on one of the ranges named Kūh-i Rang, one of the highest mountains in south-western Persia (estimated at 13,000 feet).</quote></desc>
